texts.text: >You defeat each demon as they come and reach the Mark of the Seal.
I am Taisei, son of Jogan and head of the Yamamoto Clan!
I have come to face the trial of the "Haja Blade Ritual"!
>Something emerges from the mark as Taisei finishes speaking.
I am Titan. A deity of old.
Master of the Yamamoto Clan. You shall face me in combat to test your blade!

I accept!
*Thrust*
Ah, you have the strength to wound me. Impressive.
*Strike*
As is your skill with a long sword. Almost as if you're not...
>The Liberators watch in awe as Taisei unleashes his strength.
Yo, what's the hell is goin' on? I can't see anythin'...
No human can move like that. There's something we're not getting.
Just monster vs monster now...
>However, you see Jeng Yun watching the fight closely...
>A few years ago. At the Yamamoto residence.
This is amazing! A real Japanese "katana"!
Yes. I made it too. It's my best work yet.
>Taisei presents a blade that glistens like sunlight off falling water.
Taisei, let me see.
How is it, father? This one must be good...
Hmm...
>Jogan swings the sword and gracefully cuts a straw pole in half.
That was amazing! This is an incredible sword!
Is this not unlike anything ever before, father?
Taisei, come with me...
>Jogan takes Taisei to a small creek and sticks the sword into it.
Watch that bamboo leaf as it flows down towards your sword.
>As the leaf flows towards the edge of Taisei's sword,
>it is cut in half with little effort.
This is an incredible sword. Father, you must admit it.
No, this is simply a very sharp blade.
It only takes its outward appearance into consideration,
and is a failed experiment that happens to be able to cut well.
What?! But what are swords if not cutting implements?!
Taisei... What is the mark of a truly great sword?
One that can cut down even the most ferocious enemies.
And Yamamoto Clan's purpose is to create those very objects.
Father...?
>Present day. The battle between Titan and Taisei rages on...
You have trained well, child. I acknowledge thee as being worthy.
>Spiritual energy flows into Taisei's sword.
It's... It's glowing?!
Your blade is now one step closer towards its completion.
>Titan disappears after uttering those words.
That was amazing!
Congratulations!
To be honest, I wasn't sure I would be able to win.
But I have trained hard and my power is not mine alone.
It'll be dark soon. We should keep going.
Yes. Our next stop is the Mark of the Pass. Stay on guard.
>You defeat each demon as they arrive at the Mark of the Pass.
I have come to face the trial of the "Haja Blade Ritual"!
>Something emerges from the mark as Taisei finishes speaking.
Ah, you have impeccable timing. I was just getting bored.
Nobody will fight me because they say I'm too rough on them.
I am the warrior, Berserker!
Let's see who has the better blade, you or me!
>Taisei and Berserker's sword make a loud clang as they meet.
Not bad! You stopped my first attack! This should be fun...!
>Berserker becomes enraged and begins attacking like a wild animal.
*Roar*
*Strike*
It's not working. He's not feeling any pain!
Human...! You dare leave yourself that open?!
Crap, no time to watch. We got company.
Here they come. Do not let the demons near Taisei!

*Pant*
Fine. Devil Download!
>Jeng Yun is reminded of something as he fights the demons...
My sword was perfect. Why won't he just acknowledge that...?
Taisei, you trained so hard under him too.
Do you want to stay on this path?
I'm very proud of my clan's tradition.
And I'm drawn to the idea of making enchanted swords.
This way of life suits me.
I see.
Or rather... It may be that...
I just want my father to recognize my abilities.
He's protected Tokyo as the head of this clan for so long.
I admire him very much. Yet, he refuses to return that feeling.
Regardless of how much I train...
What is it? What am I missing...?!
>As Taisei struggles to find his way through this darkness,
>Jeng Yun also struggles to find words of encouragement.
>Present day. At the Mark of the Pass.
*Strike*
>Taisei's sword cuts Berserker's blade in half!

*Laugh*
To think that my blade would be broken!

*Pant*
You've come back to your senses.
Well done. I acknowledge you as being worthy!
>Spiritual energy flows into Taisei's sword.
It's glowing even more than before...
Only the summit remains. But you have your work cut out...
What work do I have left to do...?
You don't know?! Ha! That's for you to find out then!
>Berserker disappears after uttering his warning.
Liberators, you have my thanks.
You allowed me to focus on these battles by taking care of the interlopers.
You're welcome.
Thank you too.
You and Jeng Yun seem to have that in common.
I am only fulfilling my duty.
But what did Berserker mean by what he just said? Any ideas?
I was not aware of this, but there may be something waiting for us up there.
It's nearly night. We must hurry to the summit!
